        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! Your counter is ready. Here's the wiring summary:\n\n**Wiring Table:**\n\n| Component | Arduino Pin | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| Segment A (Display) | D2 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment B (Display) | D3 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment C (Display) | D4 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment D (Display) | D5 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment E (Display) | D6 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment F (Display) | D7 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Segment G (Display) | D8 | via 220Ω resistor |\n| Display GND | GND | Common cathode |\n| Button (Increment) | D9 | Pulled LOW when pressed; uses INPUT_PULLUP |\n\n**How it works:**\n- Press the button to increment the counter from 0–9, then wrap back to 0.\n- The sketch maps each digit to its 7-segment pattern and updates the display on every button press.\n- Button press is debounced (20ms) to avoid multiple counts from a single press.\n- Current draw: ~25–35 mA (safe for Arduino Uno)."
      }
